olid;\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-2 fusion_builder_column_1_1 1_1 fusion-one-full fusion-column-first fusion-column-last\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-flex-column-wrapper-legacy\" style=\"background-position:left top;background-repeat:no-repeat;-webkit-background-size:cover;-moz-background-size:cover;-o-background-size:cover;background-size:cover;padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep\" style=\"margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;margin-top:50px;width:100%;\"><\/div><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-3\"><h3>Welcome! You're in the right place to learn how to grow succulents&#8211;wherever you live!<\/h3>\n<p>You're here because you love succulents, but you're not sure if you can grow them in your local environment.<\/p>\n<p>I totally understand! And I've got good news for you&#8230;<\/p>\n<h4>Anyone can grow succulents, no matter where they live,\u00a0and I'm going to give you the foundation you need to do just that.<\/h4>\n<p>Many people want to grow succulents but don't have the perfect growing conditions for them. In fact, I'm part of that group of people, too!<\/p>\n<p><span style=\"line-height: 28.7999992370605px;\">For some people, growing succulents is a breeze. For others, it's a daily struggle. Either way, this guide will teach you the essential components to find success growing succulents in less than ideal circumstances.<\/span><\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_6241\" style=\"width: 745px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-6241\" class=\"wp-image-6241 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/If-youve-struggled-to-grow-succulents-this-is-the-post-for-you-These-arent-tips-youve-heard-before.jpg\" alt=\"If you've struggled to grow succulents, this is the post for you! These aren't tips you've heard before!\" width=\"735\" height=\"1102\" data-pin-description=\"Succulent growing is so much fun, no matter where you live! But, you also need to know the best ways to care for your succulents. Learn how to adjust your succulent care based on your climate with the tips in this post! #succulentgrowing #succulents #succulentcare #succulent #succulentgarden #succulenttips #indoorsucculents #outdoorsucculents #growingsucculents #succulentsfromseeds #succulentandcactus #succulentsplanterspots #succulentprojects #succulentinspiration #succulenthouseplant\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/If-youve-struggled-to-grow-succulents-this-is-the-post-for-you-These-arent-tips-youve-heard-before-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/If-youve-struggled-to-grow-succulents-this-is-the-post-for-you-These-arent-tips-youve-heard-before-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/If-youve-struggled-to-grow-succulents-this-is-the-post-for-you-These-arent-tips-youve-heard-before.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><p id=\"caption-attachment-6241\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinmid=6220&awinaffid=233213&clickref=blog_anywhere&platform=dl&ued=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fsearch%3Fq%3DEcheveria%2520Lime%2520and%2520chili\">Echeveria &#8216;Lime and Chili'<\/a><\/p><\/div>\n<p>Some people say that succulents are hard to kill&#8211;but that makes me cringe a little. Like with all plants, you need to know <a href=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/growing-succulents-indoors-ebook\/\">how to care for succulents<\/a> in order to keep them alive.<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-4\"><span class=\"tve-leads-two-step-trigger tl-2step-trigger-18590\"><div class=\"fusion-aligncenter\"><style type=\"text\/css\">.fusion-button.button-1 {border-radius:0px;}<\/style><a class=\"fusion-button button-flat fusion-button-default-size button-default button-1 fusion-button-default-span fusion-button-default-type\" target=\"_self\"><span class=\"fusion-button-text\">Click here to get access to my free Succulents for Beginners course!<\/span><\/a><\/div><\/span>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep\" style=\"margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;margin-top:25px;width:100%;\"><\/div><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-5\"><p>The good news is that, compared to a lot of other kinds of plants, succulents are generally very forgiving , and easy to keep alive. It's just that in some parts of the world (or parts of your home) you'll need to use a few specialist tricks to make sure they thrive.<\/p>\n<p>In this post, I'm going to show you exactly what you need to do to help your succulents be their very best, in the easiest way possible.<\/p>\n<p>Sound good? Let's get started!<\/p>\n<h3>Pick the right plants<\/h3>\n<p>One thing I've learned over and over (from the tragic deaths of many succulents) is that some succulents grow better in my home, while others thrive outside on my porch. Most succulents won't survive the winter outside where I live (Zone 5).<\/p>\n<p>But not all succulents will do very well inside my home either. I don't have very much natural light, so a lot of my plants struggle indoors.<\/p>\n<p>If you're growing succulents outdoors you'll want to read up on how much sunlight they need. While the labels on many succulents say &#8220;full sun,&#8221; they may not tolerate 100 degree weather with direct sun all day (though some will).<\/p>\n<p>And even if they can acclimate to full sun, they'll typically need some time to get used to it if they've been purchased from a nursery where they were kept in a greenhouse.<\/p>\n<p>You'll also want to be aware of your succulents' frost tolerance. For those of us with cold winters, <a href=\"https:\/\/mountaincrestgardens.com\/sempervivum-hens-and-chicks\/?aff=2\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Sempervivums<\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/mountaincrestgardens.com\/sedum-stonecrop\/?aff=2\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">stonecrop Sedums<\/a> are our go-to outdoor succulents. I've loved being able to create potted arrangements for my porch that will survive year round and always look great!<\/p>\n<p>Those of you fortunate to live in zone 8 and above, you can pretty much have your pick of succulents! Most succulents do best in a zone 9 or 10 when outdoors.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_6248\" style=\"width: 745px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-6248\" class=\"wp-image-6248 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/If-youve-found-succulents-difficult-to-grow-these-5-tips-will-really-help-you-be-more-successful-with-your-succulent-garden.jpg\" alt=\"If you've found succulents difficult to grow, these 5 tips will really help you be more successful with your succulent garden\" width=\"735\" height=\"1102\" data-pin-description=\"Succulent growing is so much fun, no matter where you live! But, you also need to know the best ways to care for your succulents. Learn how to adjust your succulent care based on your climate with the tips in this post! #succulentgrowing #succulents #succulentcare #succulent #succulentgarden #succulenttips #indoorsucculents #outdoorsucculents #growingsucculents #succulentsfromseeds #succulentandcactus #succulentsplanterspots #succulentprojects #succulentinspiration #succulenthouseplant\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/If-youve-found-succulents-difficult-to-grow-these-5-tips-will-really-help-you-be-more-successful-with-your-succulent-garden-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/If-youve-found-succulents-difficult-to-grow-these-5-tips-will-really-help-you-be-more-successful-with-your-succulent-garden-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/If-youve-found-succulents-difficult-to-grow-these-5-tips-will-really-help-you-be-more-successful-with-your-succulent-garden.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><p id=\"caption-attachment-6248\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/types-of-succulents\/agave-victoriae-reginae-queen-victoria-agave-royal-agave\/\">Agave victoriae-reginae &#8220;Queen Victoria Agave&#8221;<\/a><\/p><\/div>\n<p>If you're growing succulents indoors and (like me) don't have a lot of natural light in your home, then you'll want to look for plants that tolerate low light. Most <a href=\"https:\/\/leafandclay.co\/products\/haworthia-fasciata?variant=28826591299?rfsn=376597.71f09\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Haworthias<\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=anywhere_gasteria&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fshop%2FCTSairplants%2Fsearch%3Fsearch_query%3Dgasteria%26order%3Ddate_desc%26view_type%3Dgallery%26ref%3Dshop_search\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Gasterias<\/a> are great in low light.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=blog&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fsearch%2Fhandmade%2Fcraft-supplies-and-tools%2Fhome-and-hobby%2Ffloral-and-garden-crafts%2Fgardening-and-plants%3Fq%3Dsansevieria%26order%3Dmost_relevant%26ref%3Dauto2%26explicit_scope%3D1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Sansevierias<\/a>\u00a0are also becoming a new favorite of mine. They need hardly any light or water.<\/p>\n<p>Sadly, you'll want to avoid <a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=anywhere_echeveria&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fpeople%2Fcameracassidy%2Ffavorites%3Fq%3Decheveria\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Echeverias<\/a> if you don't have much light. They tend to get stretched out as they try to find more light.<\/p>\n<p>In general, more colorful succulents, like <a href=\"https:\/\/mountaincrestgardens.com\/sedum-nussbaumerianum-nussbaumers-sedum-coppertone-stonecrop\/?aff=2\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Sedum\u00a0nussbaumerianum<\/a>, need plenty of light to maintain their color. Succulents that are naturally green tend to be happier indoors.<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-6\"><span class=\"tve-leads-two-step-trigger tl-2step-trigger-18590\"><div class=\"fusion-aligncenter\"><style type=\"text\/css\">.fusion-button.button-2 {border-radius:0px;}<\/style><a class=\"fusion-button button-flat fusion-button-default-size button-default button-2 fusion-button-default-span fusion-button-default-type\" target=\"_self\"><span class=\"fusion-button-text\">Click here to get access to my free Succulents for Beginners course!<\/span><\/a><\/div><\/span>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep\" style=\"margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;margin-top:25px;width:100%;\"><\/div><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-7\"><p>If you tend to over water, try to find succulents that are forgiving of over-watering, or that need more water. Since <a href=\"https:\/\/mountaincrestgardens.com\/portulacaria-afra-green-elephant-bush-miniature-jade\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Portulacaria afra<\/a> has thin leaves I've found it needs to be watered more often. <a href=\"https:\/\/mountaincrestgardens.com\/crassula-arborescens-subsp-undulatifolia-ripple-jade\/?aff=2\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Crassula arborescens undulatifolia<\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=anywhere_zwartkop&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Flisting%2F150372091%2Fsucculent-plant-black-rose-aeonium%3Fga_order%3Dmost_relevant%26ga_search_type%3Dall%26ga_view_type%3Dgallery%26ga_search_query%3Daeonium%2520zwartkop%26ref%3Dsr_gallery_7\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Aeonium zwartkop<\/a> are two others I've found to need more water.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_6246\" style=\"width: 745px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-6246\" class=\"wp-image-6246 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Portulacaria-afra-is-a-great-succulent-for-growing-indoors-and-out-find-out-how-to-grow-this-succulent-and-others-no-matter-where-you-live.jpg\" alt=\"Portulacaria afra is a great succulent for growing indoors and out - find out how to grow this succulent and others no matter where you live\" width=\"735\" height=\"490\" data-pin-description=\"Succulent growing is so much fun, no matter where you live! But, you also need to know the best ways to care for your succulents. Learn how to adjust your succulent care based on your climate with the tips in this post! #succulentgrowing #succulents #succulentcare #succulent #succulentgarden #succulenttips #indoorsucculents #outdoorsucculents #growingsucculents #succulentsfromseeds #succulentandcactus #succulentsplanterspots #succulentprojects #succulentinspiration #succulenthouseplant\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Portulacaria-afra-is-a-great-succulent-for-growing-indoors-and-out-find-out-how-to-grow-this-succulent-and-others-no-matter-where-you-live-500x333.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Portulacaria-afra-is-a-great-succulent-for-growing-indoors-and-out-find-out-how-to-grow-this-succulent-and-others-no-matter-where-you-live-700x467.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Portulacaria-afra-is-a-great-succulent-for-growing-indoors-and-out-find-out-how-to-grow-this-succulent-and-others-no-matter-where-you-live.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><p id=\"caption-attachment-6246\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/types-of-succulents\/portulacaria-afra-elephant-bush\/\">Portulacaria afra &#8220;Elephant Bush&#8221;<\/a><\/p><\/div>\n<p>On the other hand, really plump succulents like <a href=\"https:\/\/mountaincrestgardens.com\/graptoveria-fred-ives\/?aff=2\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Graptoveria &#8216;Fred Ives'<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=blog&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fsearch%3Fq%3Dpachyveria%2520glauca%2520in%2520garden%2520and%2520plants\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Pachyveria glauca<\/a>, and <a href=\"http:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=anywhere_succulentoasis&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Flisting%2F271343216%2Fmature-aloe-hybrid-brevifolia-x-humilis%3Fga_order%3Dmost_relevant%26ga_search_type%3Dall%26ga_view_type%3Dgallery%26ga_search_query%3Daloe%2520brevifolia%26ref%3Dsr_gallery-1-8\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Aloe brevifolia<\/a> can go much longer before needing water again. You'll also find that cacti, such as <a href=\"http:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=blog&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fsearch%3Fq%3DMammillaria%2520rhodantha%2520in%2520garden%2520and%2520plants\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Mammillaria rhodantha<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=blog&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fsearch%3Fq%3DMammillaria%2520gracilis%2520fragilis%2520in%2520garden%2520and%2520plants\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Mammillaria gracilis fragilis<\/a>, are very tolerant of long periods of drought.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_6242\" style=\"width: 745px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-6242\" class=\"wp-image-6242 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Thick-leaved-succulents-can-go-longer-between-watering-that-thinner-leaved-succulents.jpg\" alt=\"Thick leaved succulents can go longer between watering that thinner leaved succulents\" width=\"735\" height=\"490\" data-pin-description=\"Succulent growing is so much fun, no matter where you live! But, you also need to know the best ways to care for your succulents. Learn how to adjust your succulent care based on your climate with the tips in this post! #succulentgrowing #succulents #succulentcare #succulent #succulentgarden #succulenttips #indoorsucculents #outdoorsucculents #growingsucculents #succulentsfromseeds #succulentandcactus #succulentsplanterspots #succulentprojects #succulentinspiration #succulenthouseplant\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Thick-leaved-succulents-can-go-longer-between-watering-that-thinner-leaved-succulents-500x333.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Thick-leaved-succulents-can-go-longer-between-watering-that-thinner-leaved-succulents-700x467.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Thick-leaved-succulents-can-go-longer-between-watering-that-thinner-leaved-succulents.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><p id=\"caption-attachment-6242\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"><a href=\"http:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=anywhere_succulentoasis&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Flisting%2F271343216%2Fmature-aloe-hybrid-brevifolia-x-humilis%3Fga_order%3Dmost_relevant%26ga_search_type%3Dall%26ga_view_type%3Dgallery%26ga_search_query%3Daloe%2520brevifolia%26ref%3Dsr_gallery-1-8\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Aloe brevifolia<\/a><\/p><\/div>\n<p>Are you catching on here? Plant selection can be a major factor in the success of your succulent garden. To learn more about choosing the best succulents for where you live, sign up for my free course, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/succulents-for-beginners\/\">Succulents for Beginners<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>If you don't know what kind of succulents you own, I'll help you learn how to identify them in <a href=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/3-ways-to-identify-your-succulents\/\">this post<\/a>.<\/p>\n<h3>Tweak your soil materials<\/h3>\n<p>I've had quite a few people email me to ask how to grow succulents in a humid environment &#8212; or in a super dry one. Success in both these cases comes down to choosing the right soil.<\/p>\n<p>In humid areas, soil plays a major role in preventing rot. On the other hand, in dry environments the right soil can help prevent succulents from drying out too quickly.<\/p>\n<p>Here is my basic recommendation for making your own well-draining\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/well-draining-soil-for-succulent-container-gardens\/\">succulent soil<\/a>. You can also purchase a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.bonsaijack.com\/Succulent_Soil_sas.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">great mix here<\/a>.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_13127\" style=\"width: 745px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-13127\" class=\"wp-image-13127 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/Bonsai-Jack-soil-mix-is-perfect-for-indoor-succulents.jpg\" alt=\"Bonsai Jack soil mix is perfect for indoor succulents\" width=\"735\" height=\"1103\" data-pin-description=\"Succulent growing is so much fun, no matter where you live! But, you also need to know the best ways to care for your succulents. Learn how to adjust your succulent care based on your climate with the tips in this post! #succulentgrowing #succulents #succulentcare #succulent #succulentgarden #succulenttips #indoorsucculents #outdoorsucculents #growingsucculents #succulentsfromseeds #succulentandcactus #succulentsplanterspots #succulentprojects #succulentinspiration #succulenthouseplant\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/Bonsai-Jack-soil-mix-is-perfect-for-indoor-succulents-53x80.jpg 53w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/Bonsai-Jack-soil-mix-is-perfect-for-indoor-succulents-200x300.jpg 200w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/Bonsai-Jack-soil-mix-is-perfect-for-indoor-succulents-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/Bonsai-Jack-soil-mix-is-perfect-for-indoor-succulents-400x600.jpg 400w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/Bonsai-Jack-soil-mix-is-perfect-for-indoor-succulents-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/Bonsai-Jack-soil-mix-is-perfect-for-indoor-succulents-585x878.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/Bonsai-Jack-soil-mix-is-perfect-for-indoor-succulents-600x900.jpg 600w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/Bonsai-Jack-soil-mix-is-perfect-for-indoor-succulents-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/Bonsai-Jack-soil-mix-is-perfect-for-indoor-succulents.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><p id=\"caption-attachment-13127\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"><a href=\"https:\/\/mountaincrestgardens.com\/echeveria-lola?aff=2\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\">Echeveria &#8216;Lola'<\/a> planted in <a href=\"https:\/\/www.bonsaijack.com\/category\/premixed-bonsai-soil\/succulent-soil\/?utm_source=succulentsandsunshine.com&utm_medium=referral\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\">Bonsai Jack Succulent Soil<\/a><\/p><\/div>\n<p>The mix mentioned above is great for growing succulents, indoors and out, in containers. But if you really tend to over-water, or if you live in a humid environment, I highly recommend planting in just one material: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.bonsaijack.com\/aggregate_bonsai_pumice_quarter_inch_sas.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\">pumice<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>This is the\u00a0 most universally available product that retains some water but also dries out quickly. I know of several succulent growers that plant only in pumice, and have huge success with it. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.bonsaijack.com\/bonsai_jack_homesas.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\">Bonsai Jack<\/a> carries a great quality pumice (1\/4&#8243; particles, which is ideal) but you can get it at most nurseries, too.<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-8\"><span class=\"tve-leads-two-step-trigger tl-2step-trigger-18590\"><div class=\"fusion-aligncenter\"><style type=\"text\/css\">.fusion-button.button-3 {border-radius:0px;}<\/style><a class=\"fusion-button button-flat fusion-button-default-size button-default button-3 fusion-button-default-span fusion-button-default-type\" target=\"_self\"><span class=\"fusion-button-text\">Click here to get access to my free Succulents for Beginners course!<\/span><\/a><\/div><\/span>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator fusion-full-width-sep\" style=\"margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto;margin-top:25px;width:100%;\"><\/div><div class=\"fusion-sep-clear\"><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-9\"><p>While drying out very quickly isn't the worst problem to have, no one wants to water succulents every other day, right? One of the great things about succulents is their\u00a0drought tolerance, but they do still need water to survive.<\/p>\n<p>A great options for hot and dry climates, or if you find your soil dries out too quickly, is <a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/2iBFaZj\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\">coconut coir<\/a>. This medium retains a lot of water but also drains well so it doesn't get soggy like standard peat based potting soil.<\/p>\n<h3>Choose a great pot<\/h3>\n<p>The material of your pot can also play a big role in how well your succulent survives. Terra cotta is a great choice if you're just starting out, because it's very porous, allowing more air flow to the roots. This means the soil will dry out more quickly.<\/p>\n<p>If you live in a very hot, dry environment, though, terra cotta may not be the best choice. Ceramics are generally a good option for most climates. You'll find a great selection of pots to purchase on <a href=\"https:\/\/mountaincrestgardens.com\/pots-for-succulents?aff=2\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\">Mountain Crest Gardens<\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=anywhere_pottery&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fpeople%2Fcameracassidy%2Ffavorites%2Ffavorite-pottery%3Fref%3Dfavs_index_12\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\">Etsy<\/a>.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_6247\" style=\"width: 745px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-6247\" class=\"wp-image-6247 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/Terra-cotta-is-such-a-great-choice-for-growing-succulents.jpg\" alt=\"Terra cotta is such a great choice for growing succulents\" width=\"735\" height=\"1102\" data-pin-description=\"Succulent growing is so much fun, no matter where you live! But, you also need to know the best ways to care for your succulents. Learn how to adjust your succulent care based on your climate with the tips in thi